Description:
Stylish and Spacious in Leafy Beauty
Hidden behind a high fence and a towering Jacaranda tree, this casual 2 bedroom street front residence is made to meet your lifestyle needs.
With the ease of polished boards and 2 stylish alfresco courtyards, this sun filled retreat features a north facing living room with adjoining dining area, modern kitchen with stainless steel appliances, 2 double bedrooms (BIRs), updated retro bathroom, separate toilet and fitted laundry.
Easy to live in or let out, this homely haven features a security porch, double blinds, low voltage lighting, ducted heating, an air conditioner and a lock up garage with 2nd car space on drive. In the McKinnon Secondary College zone, a short walk to North Road shops, cafes, train, Ormond Primary School and Monash University bus.

Description:
***UNDER OFFER*** Courtyard charisma in a class of its own
Superbly located and in a quiet street, this enchanting apartment offers so much more than meets the eye! Immaculately presented with polished floors throughout, it offers bright, modern kitchen and meals and central living with reverse cycle heating and cooling highlighted by a stunning, tropical inspired courtyard with elevated timber deck and generous pebbled entertaining area. Two robed bedrooms enjoy a tranquil garden outlook, while the stylish and spacious bathroom offers shower over bath plus separate WC. Also featuring secure intercom entry, a handy garden shed and single carport with access via courtyard, just moments from public transport and North Road shops and cafes - this lovingly created home ensures your search is finally over!

Description:
SOLD by Tom Grieve
Stylishly renovated creating modern impact with its dark timber floors offset by crisp white walls, this funky 1st floor 2 bedroom security apartment is the retreat for all reasons.
Completely secure, this dynamic starter features relaxing living & dining, 2 large bedrooms (BIRs), bright north facing kitchen (provision for dishwasher/washing machine) and a sparkling fully tiled bathroom. With every modern comfort, it boasts R/C air conditioning, great storage, intercom, option of communal laundry & auto gates to a carport.
On the edge of North Road shops with an up and coming group of shops, organic goods, cafes and transport, with easy access to both Monash University campuses as well as the city train, it's a fabulous starter or investment any way you look at it.

Description:
Faded gem awaits a fantastic future
Retaining some stunning features from its circa 1920 heritage and a facade that will make your imagination soar, this ideally located 3 bedroom period beauty on an outstanding 676sqm approx now offers an exciting opportunity for total transformation (STCA). Currently comprising entry into lounge and adjoining dining, separate kitchen, bathroom with bath and shower and external laundry and WC, plus a deep, private rear garden.
Be inspired by the superb neighbouring properties and create your own Californian dream, with options to go up, extend into the deep rear garden or perhaps even a pool for endless summer fun! With excellent access to North Rd shops and restaurants, parklands, trains, buses and quality schools nearby, here's a large scale opportunity to fulfill your renovating ambition!

Description:
Modern prestige in a prime pocket
A symphony of modern grace and timeless elegance, this spectacular low-maintenance masterpiece has been crafted without compromise creating a family environment of comfort and luxury. With its own street frontage and driveway, generous proportions are welcomed by stunning parquetry flooring throughout lounge and dining rooms preceding a gourmet Stone kitchen with Bosch appliances setting superb tone for an easy-care semi-covered entertaining courtyard. A downstairs guest bedroom and full bathroom is accompanied upstairs by 3 further robed bedrooms (main with quality ensuite and WIR), spacious family bathroom and retreat/rumpus room. Setting the standard in private stress-free living and finished to the highest caliber with alarm system, ducted heating and vacuum, split system cooling,
under stair storage, Stone finishes throughout and double garage with internal access, superbly located a short walk to train station, shops, Glen Huntly Primary and Kilvington.

Description:
Zone in on a Joyce Park position
Walk to school on weekdays, spend weekends in the park, enjoy the rewards of this exceptional McKinnon College Zone address every day! Backing Joyce Park in one of the College Zone's best streets, this approx 655sqm property offers a lifetime of benefits with the back gate of the College within a 200m walk, the Primary School within a few blocks and the North Road bus and Ormond's strip and station within a walk.
Whether it's a family dream home or visionary dual occupancy development (Subject to Council Approval), this prime site has the perfect proportions (approx 15.24m by 42.98m) and sunny northerly rear orientation to make a designing a successful home a walk in the park. Offered with a rentable up to four bedroom period home with outbuildings, second WC and open-garage, there's even potential for this super-site to pay its way through the planning process.
Surrounded by quality renovations and luxury new homes, backed by the Park and a minute's walk to the College, this is anything but an everyday Zone opportunity.

Description:
1930's Beauty meets Poolside Life in the Zone
A rare opportunity to secure a spacious 5 Bedroom 2 bathroom residence on a single level, all in the McKinnon College zone!
Set on a large 720 Sq Metre block, and sitting on the high side of one of Ormond Hill's finest streets, this renovated and extended 1930's family home features:
An exceptionally well-zoned floor plan with parents bedroom and formal rooms to the front and children's bedrooms in a rear wing large formal lounge and dining rooms including glorious Art Deco detail, with tapestry-brick fireplaces, decorative ceilings, rich original timber work,
Expansive open plan eating and north facing family rooms
A newly renovated kitchen with Caesar Stone benches and Bosch appliances,
Polished porcelain bathrooms,
Climate controlled comfort throughout with central heating & cooling,
reverse-cycle air-conditioned to master bedroom
multiple ceiling fans.
Step outside the modern French doors from the family room and you will find a beautifully finished north facing poolside living area including :
- an elevated deck constructed with timber recycled from Melbourne's original Docklands
- a fan-cooled and heated al fresco area providing for year round outdoor dining
- Extensive outdoor kitchen including large BBQ and Wok Burner, Sink and bar fridge provision
- Invisible glass fencing to allow all-round views through to a 10 meter kid-safe pool, and immaculately groomed, secluded private garden with space to play
This property has dual access which is a rarity for this locality. The double gates at the rear provide easy and convenient access to the Ruby St Cul de Sac, with the Ormond Primary School boundary in less than 100 meters. The concealed brick area behind the poolside garden provides an ideal space boat or trailer parking.

Description:
SEVENTIES SINGLE LEVEL SOLID BRICK HOME SITUATED IN A CUL-DE-SAC WITH HUGE POTENITAL IN THE MCKINNON
Take possession of this classic seventies brick home located high on the McKinnon Hill, in a quiet cul-de sac. With a generous block of approx 470 sqm, and a north facing back yard, you too can capitalise on the McKinnon School Zone location, and create your dream home.
Featuring 3 good sized bedrooms, with BIR, L shaped lounge and kitchen/meals area, and a classic U shape design as well as a double carport.
Go up, renovate, or remove to create a grand platform for a new single or double story home (STCA).
Walking distance to Ormond Primary, Allnutt Park and Wattle Grove Reserve all within immediate access. Enjoy a latte at McKinnon Village, or access the supermarkets and shops Centre Rd has to offer. Zone 1 train at McKinnon, either way a great recipe for a promising future.
View by appointment or scheduled open times.
Conjunctional with Eric Cohen Real Estate

Description:
Sunny, Secluded & in a Small Group
It's all about, sun, serenity and perfect privacy here! First-floor to the rear of this boutique group of just six, this renovated two bedroom apartment makes the most of its quiet rear position with an entry shared with only the downstairs, a private stairway and a neighbour-free position with no shared walls. Showcasing a quality renovation with a glittering CaesarStone and European appliance kitchen including stainless-steel dishwasher, this tranquil apartment features a fresh white bathroom with laundry facilities, a separate WC, solid Oak parquetry-style floors throughout and ducyed heating & refrigerated air-conditioning.
Filled with natural light with north-facing living, there are great extras including streamlined built-in robes, intercom entry and a carport on title. Located just a few blocks from Ormond's shopping and station with parklands close, this peaceful rear apartment is the perfect place for first-home buyers to get their piece of the market or for investors to find peace of mind!

Description:
SOLD by Tom Grieve
Enjoying the serenity of its own surrounds, this savvy ground floor 1 bedroom security apartment has all the space you could want with warm and inviting flair.
With a stylish indoor outdoor feel, this easy care retreat features an entry hall, open plan entertaining with galley style kitchen featuring Ariston appliances and stone benchtops, large bedroom (BIRs), sleek bathroom with marble vanity and Euro laundry. Relax in the tranquil courtyard with its decked fencing and morning sun warmth, this groovy number features security entry, R/C air conditioning, security basement parking + storage cage.
In a fantastic location, a casual stroll to North Road shops, cafes and restaurants, train and Monash Uni bus.

Description:
Above & Beyond on the Streetfront!
This one takes street front living to a new level. Master built to an outstanding standard, this three bedroom plus fitted study, 2.5 bathroom, dual zone home goes above and beyond prestige living with an elite Bosch kitchen, fully tiled bathrooms (including a dual vanity ensuite), CaesarStone benchtops (even for the laundry) and a mix of wideboard timber flooring and plush carpets. With all the accoutrements of luxury living, this climate controlled home features ducting vacuum, video intercom entry and an oversize double auto garage with parking in front.
But it's not just the finish that puts this home above all others. Sized up to an extraordinary standard, the home features vast formal and casual living zones, a north facing deck and super sized double bedrooms including master with walk-behind robe... plus more flexible spaces including a study area and a flexible retreat area large enough to fit a small sofa.
Even the location goes above and beyond - just a walk to shops and station with the North Rd and Grange Rd bus services just around the corner.
